name: Hindhede Nature Park
review_text: The goal was to visit the ex-quarry that’s currently a serene lake with surrounding fauna and wild insects, birds and animals. A good walk to get fresh air, easy accessible and short trail to the quarry. There’s also a mountain bike trail, don’t use that for walking.

name: Hindhede Nature Park
review_text:
18 Jan 2022:  Visit #2…Pretty easy trail, scenic, serene and you get to enjoy birds chirping and the magnificent view of Hindhede Quarry.

23 Aug 2021: Nice small park for all and Hindhede Nature Park is next to Bukit Timah Nature Reserve. The trail is not too difficult, we get to breathe fresh air and also enjoy the amazing flora and fauna. This is also a good place for bird watching and the view of Hindhede Quarry is truly awesome. For those who plan to drive; please take note that finding a parking space can be very challenging.

name: Hindhede Nature Park

Followed the link bridge will reached Gaharu Hut then turned left walked further up will be Waringin Hut from there followed pathway will reached Hindhede Quarry Lookout Point. The purpose of today visited is to view Hindhede Quarry + tried hiking another path to reach Bukit Timah Hill Summit. Am satisfied to explore the South View Path,whereby need to climb 'endless' of stairs

name: Hindhede Nature Park

One of the most relaxing place we had visited.

This place is well shadded with boardwalk and footpath and several hut for resting.

We intended to visit the Hindhede Quarry but was disappointed to know that it was under repair upon arrival but the good news is the completion date is 30 November 2022.

There is a kids playground and an exercise area.

We prepared food and had our picnic in Waringin Hut when we noticed that we got company dining with us in close proximity.

name: Hindhede Nature Park
review_text:
Hindhede Nature Park, a peaceful simple well maintain park which is great for family with kids and elderly.
Officially opened by Mr Mah Bow Tan on 17th August 2001.
Comes with a playground / picnic area and even with a foot reflexology path.
A small look out platform which is an excellent spot for photographer and bird watching.
Simply relaxing trekking park with quite a number of huts for resting.

name: Hindhede Nature Park
review_text:
Hindhede Quarry and other quarries in the surrounding areas used to be where granite mining took place in Singapore since the 1900s. But this ended in the 1980s, leaving behind the best nature has to offer and was renamed as Hindhede Nature Park. The park was officially opened by Mr. Mah Bow Tan, the Minister for National Development on 17 Aug 2001. It has gorgeous walking trails, fitness park and playground.  Other activities include jogging, hiking and bird watching. This quarry has a beautiful lake with a maximum depth of18 metres.
It is located next to Bukit Timah Nature Reserve. With easy trails and well-defined footpaths, the park is ideal for families with young children and the elderly.

name: Hindhede Nature Park

Morning is probably the best time to visit where you can see turtles and an unreal reflection of the opposite cliff, almost like a mirror reflection.

A unique and good place to escape from busy urban environment. The famous HINDHEDE QUARRY is filled with water becaming a nice view. There was a total of 25 granite quarries in Singapore.

Here is a brief about HINDHEDE QUARRY  according to the info board in the park.

The rock face surrounding the quarry
pond is part of the Bukit Timah granite
complex, which was crystallised from
magma beneath the Earth's surface some 200 million years ago, during the early to mid Triassic age. Through a small pocket of tin deposit was found in Bukit Panjang Quarry, it was the granite rocks that were of economic value to Singapore.

review_text:
The Good: pretty nice view of a quarry.

The Not So Great: Compared to others, pretty poor airflow, dense and humid. Not sure why but there seems to be quite abit of trash lying about. Unlucky to run into birdwatchers/bird photographers sometimes set up their tripods and hog the entire view. I don't mind them but these folks did not get hint to move aside so that others may share the view.  Playground is in disrepair and unusable. We saw zero kids there. And extremely limited parking space since the Bukit Timah Hill side attracts alot of visitors. There are no alternative parking lots nearby.

Verdict: Many beautiful alternatives in Singapore. So unless you've been to those multiple times... Give this a miss!

name: Hindhede Nature Park
review_text:
For those who are looking to walk the dairy farm loop for the first time, here’s some tips :)
- entrance is slightly before the summit point; if you take the stairs up, you would need to walk 100m down from summit along the slope to see it.
- duration as stated on the sign is 1-1.5 hours for the entire loop. For people who exercise regularly, it would take 45min; for those who are very fit, possible to finish in 20-30min.
- after coming down the regas path, you can choose to go right or left to start the dairy farm loop. For those who really want to work their muscles, go right as you would be descending gently before climbing countless steps upwards after the dairy farm hut. For those who are starting out, take the left as you would be descending the challenging part and making a gentle ascent.
- there are 2 huts along the way, north view and dairy farm hut. If you go right when starting out, you would pass by dairy farm hut first; if you want to exit the path, turn right at the dairy farm hut to go out to the wallace/quarry/ rail mall, otherwise turn left to continue with the loop.
- there’s no water point and toilets, the nearest one would be at the wallace area, which is accessible mid point at the trail, from the dairy farm hut.
- for someone who is prone to mosquito bites, I must say there is really no real need to spray the insect repellant, because there are a lot of people who sprayed that and you could smell it from some distance away anyway and be protected by it. The rampant use of insect repellant has caused some plants and insects to die out over the years, so do your part for nature if possible. The only area that you need to be careful of for mosquito bites, is the steep stairs leading up to the summit from the visitor center.
- the reception is quite good inside the trail.
- there’s a lot of squirrels moving around and you could hear their distinctive sounds.
- it’s not sunny at all inside the trail, in fact this applies to the whole bukit timah hill, as there is enough canopy to block out most of the sunlight. Hence, even if you want to trek in the afternoon, it’s pretty cooling as well so no worries there.
- shoes wise, normal sports shoes work for me, no real need for proper hiking shoes.

For the park itself,
- entrance is free, except for parking.
- there’s vending machines for snacks and drinks at the entrance
- there’s toilets as well and they are fairly clean.

After the hike,
- you can choose to refuel at the beauty world food centre, bukit timah food centre, or the chuntin road stretch.
- there’s buses to other food centers nearby as well, such as Adam road and Clementi.

Hope this helps!

review_text:
(Translated by Google) A very clear natural park, a good place for leisure hiking and photography, with fresh air and beautiful environment.

name: Hindhede Nature Park
review_text:
(Translated by Google) A very beautiful place. Trekking routes of different lengths (we have only covered the shortest one so far). Lake on the site of a former granite quarry. Many animals. Small museum.

(Original)
Очень красивое место. Маршруты для трекинга разной длины (мы пока прошли только самую короткую). Озеро на месте бывшего гранитного карьера. Много животных. Небольшой музей.

name: Hindhede Nature Park
review_text:
(Translated by Google) Enter the Bukit Timah parking lot or the alleyway behind the visitor centre. It's a flat and short trail, so it's easy going.
Ahead is the pond after mining

ブキッティマの駐車場又はビジターセンター裏の小道を入ります。平らでかつ短いトレイルなので気楽に行けます。
先は採掘後の池

name: Hindhede Nature Park
review_text:

I like this small world very much. The lake water is light blue, and the tree trunks poured into the lake are very leisurely fish. The water turtle presents a very special scene in the water.
